    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but what if the morning never comes? i'm just so drained by the constant effort of being me. it feels like i'm just pouring energy into a bottomless pit. sometimes it feels less like a \"storm\" and more like just... an endless, exhausting weight. like, what if the only way to actually stop the pain and finally find some peace isn't through fighting, but just by letting go of it all? it almost sounds peaceful to just not have to struggle anymore.",
